[cm]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
Was she always this calm? [r]
Back then, she seemed more mature, but there was a stubbornness about her. She had a determination to never give in, even in desperate situations. [l][r]

Of course, in this modern world overflowing with stuff, there's no need for such determination. But still, I wonder... [r]
No, let's stop thinking about it. If I keep overthinking, Chi might not be able to relax and talk. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
I spoke little but tried to be as friendly as possible while ordering from the waiter and waiting for the food. We ate slowly and finally finished our meal together after a long time. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[bg time="2000" method="crossfade" storage="cafe1.jpg"]
[tb_show_message_window]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
On the now cleared table, two cups of coffee were letting off steam. [l][r]
I lightly touched my cup, feeling a sense of gratitude for its warmth, and looked into Chi's slightly lowered black eyes. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

