[tb_start_text mode=3]
Their supplies run at the food production facility (with an unkindly drawn map that had frustrated them). [r]
The black grave. The crumbling communication tower. The fish production facility. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[bg time="1000" method="crossfade" storage="gensen.jpg"]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
The giant train. Mysterious creatures. Humanoid weapons. [r]
The nuclear submarine. Things that roam the world processing energy. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[bg time="1000" method="crossfade" storage="bigwall.jpg"]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
The time they got injured. The replica museum. The clothes they made. [r]
The tower's AI and its 'self-destruction'. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[bg time="1000" method="crossfade" storage="gear.jpg"]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
The rocket that never launched. The grand library. The vehicle breakdown and abandonment. And the inevitable acceptance of death. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[bg time="2000" method="crossfade" storage="rasen.jpg"]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
She spoke plainly, about throwing away their gun, burning their diary, and climbing the spiral staircase with one last explosive as hope. [l][r]
She spoke of those sorrowful yet tender days, with a tone that felt somewhat nostalgic. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[bg time="3000" method="crossfade" storage="penag.jpg"]
