A single tear fell down the cheek of the girl who had lifted her face. [l][r]
I felt it probably wasn't a tear of sadness. That was what I wanted to believe. [l][r]
The coffee had gone completely cold. [r]
But I didn't ask for a refill. Cold coffee was too much of a luxury for us who had once drunk almost anything, including recycled water. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

