[tb_start_text mode=3]
After slowly finishing her coffee, Chi said, [r]
"I think I didn't wake up after that. ...The next time I came to, I was in my room, on my bed." [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3]
"I was the same... in a way." [r]
Silence filled the space. The quiet BGM of the restaurant seemed to emphasize the silence even more. [l][r]
For some reason, I couldn't speak. Even though there was something I wanted to ask the most, I couldn't bring myself to ask Chi about it. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[bg time="1000" method="crossfade" storage="rest2.jpg"]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
"...Hey," [r]
Chi broke the silence first. [r]
"Ishii, there’s something I really want to ask you." [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3]
"Sure, what is it?" [r]
"Ishii... have you ever seen a corpse?" [r]
"What...?" [l][r]
"I have. Three years ago, I saw my maternal grandfather's body in the coffin." [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[bg time="1000" method="crossfade" storage="isiChit.jpg"]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
What is Chi talking about...? [r]
I looked into her eyes, but I couldn’t understand anything just by that. [l][r]
"But in that other world, I don’t have any memory of 'seeing a corpse.' [r]
Ishii, have you?" [r]
Chi stopped there and stared straight into my eyes. [l][r]
" ...No. Now that you mention it, indeed not. I thought there was something odd in that world's logic comparing with the norms and rules of this one..." [l][r]
That’s how I answered. Chi clasped her hands together lightly and cast her gaze down at them. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
"But isn't it explainable? Or at least, it doesn't seem like a problem not to be. [l]
It wouldn’t be strange if there are things and rules in that world that don’t exist in this one." [r]
Trying to break the silence again, I said the first words that came to mind. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

